# Static-analysis baseline for the manual `tidy` target and the
# -DENABLE_CLANG_TIDY=ON per-compile mode (cmake/ClangTools.cmake).
#
# Readability checks that fight the house style are off: guard clauses
# are written without braces, protocol codecs are full of wire-format
# constants, and short names (it, w, rc) are idiomatic here. Recursion
# is used deliberately (nested/grouped TLVs).
#
# Generated trees (diam/gen, gtp/v*/gen) override this file with their
# own .clang-tidy; SWIG wrapper targets are opted out where they are
# defined (bindings/CMakeLists.txt).
---
Checks: >
  bugprone-*,
  clang-analyzer-*,
  misc-*,
  performance-*,
  portability-*,
  readability-*,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters,
  -misc-no-recursion,
  -readability-braces-around-statements,
  -readability-else-after-return,
  -readability-function-cognitive-complexity,
  -readability-identifier-length,
  -readability-isolate-declaration,
  -readability-magic-numbers,
  -clang-analyzer-security.insecureAPI.DeprecatedOrUnsafeBufferHandling
WarningsAsErrors: ''
HeaderFilterRegex: '/(task|net|sip|sdp|rtp|xfrm|diam)/inc/|/gtp/(u|v1|v2)/inc/|/bindings/cxx/inc/'
FormatStyle: file
...
